			<div class="text-left box" id="safety">
				<h2>
					Keeping Yourself and Others Safe
				</h2>
				<div>
					<span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
						Leave a 6-foot space between yourself and others.<br/>
					</span>
					<p>
						Six feet is roughly 2-3 strides, and it's the recommended distance to maintain between yourself and others.
						However, <a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-passes-between-people-6-feet-apart-2020">new guidelines</a>
						suggest that we maintain more than six feet.
					</p>
					<span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
						Wash your hands frequently.<br/>
					</span>
					<p>
						Soap can break down the protective layer of viruses and wash them away. The process takes 20 seconds.<br/>
						Twenty seconds is like...
						<ul>
							<li>Singing "Happy Birthday" twice</li>
							<li>Singing the chorus to "Lose Yourself" by Eminem twice</li>
							<li>Singing the chorus to "Take on Me" by A-Ha</li>
							<li>Singing the chorus to "Stayin' Alive" by Bee Gees</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
					<span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
						Stay home, save lives.<br/>
					</span>
					<p>
						Staying home prevents the spread of the virus to other people.<br/>
						<ul>
							<li>Even if you don't exhibit symptoms, you may still carry the virus.</li>
							<li>Please limit your daily travel to <b>essential</b> activities, such as grocery shopping.</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
					<span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
						Don't touch your face.<br/>
					</span>
					<p>
						This is how the virus enters your body.
					</p>
					<span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
						Cover your mouth when you cough or sneeze.<br/>
					</span>
					<p>
						<ul>
							<li>When you cough, droplets can spread as far as 20 feet (~6 meters).</li>
							<li>When you sneeze, droplets can spread as far as 25 feet (~8 meters).</li>
						</ul>
						<a href="https://www.sciencefocus.com/the-human-body/how-far-do-coughs-and-sneezes-travel/">Source</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
