					Donating to hospitals in need
				</h2>
				<div>
					<p>Currently, many hospitals have a shortage of <b>ventilators and personal protective equipment (PPEs).</b>
					PPEs (surgical masks, gloves, faceshields) are essential to protect the healthcare workers that are fighting on the front lines.
					Help fight COVID-19 by donating to your local hospital and providing essential protective equipment to healthcare workers.</p>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<a href="https://foundation.inova.org/covid-19-how-can-i-help/">The Inova Health Foundation COVID-19 page</a>
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="https://www.directrelief.org/emergency/coronavirus-outbreak/">Direct Relief:</a> a nonprofit that is expanding its coronavirus response efforts through the large-scale provision of PPE and other medical essentials.
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="https://www.projectn95.org/">Project N95:</a> a nonprofit organization that distributes N95 masks, surgical gloves, face shields, and other PPEs to local hospitals in need.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="text-left box" id="mask">
				<h2>How to make a mask</h2>
				We're glad you're interested in making a mask! Masks are important in places where it's difficult to maintain social distancing, e.g. grocery stores and pharmacies.<br/>
				<b>IMPORTANT:</b> The public should <i>not</i> purchase N95 masks or surgical masks; there is a shortage and healthcare workers need those masks to protect themselves.<br/>
				<b>Another note:</b> Wearing a mask isn't a substitute for social distancing.<br/>

				<h4>Method 1: The Old T-shirt Method</h4>
				<p>Materials: T-shirt and scissors</p>
				<ol>
					<li>
						Cut 7-8 inches from the bottom of a shirt.<br/>
						<img src="/img/facemask-instructions-tshirt-01.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Cut a 6-7 inch rectangle from the side of the cutout, leaving thin strips of cloth above and below. Cut the strips of cloth.<br/>
						<img src="/img/facemask-instructions-tshirt-02.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Use the strips of cloth to secure the mask to your face.<br/>
						<img src="/img/facemask-instructions-tshirt-03.png" width=512>
					</li>
				</ol>
				<h4>Method 2: The Bandanna Method</h4>
				<p>Materials: A bandanna (or other 20in. x 20in. cloth), rubber bands (or hair ties), scissors.</p>
				<ol>
					<li>
						Fold bandanna in half lengthwise.<br/>
						<img src="/img/Bandanna-Mask-01.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Fold the top down, and the bottom up.<br/>
						<img src="/img/Bandanna-Mask-02.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Place the rubber bands around the folded bandanna, about 6 inches apart.<br/>
						<img src="/img/Bandanna-Mask-03.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Fold the sides in, folding the rubber bands into the bandanna.<br/>
						<img src="/img/Bandanna-Mask-04.png" width=512>
					</li>
					<li>
						Wear the mask by putting the rubber bands around your ears, and you're done!
					</li>
				</ol>
				<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/diy-cloth-face-coverings.html">
					Source: CDC
				</a>
			</div>
